text: I'd be interested in a glass... Missed my opportunity on the hoodie.
BTW... Michigan has some of the best craft breweries. I'm hoping to get up there this summer. Bell's and Founders are first on the list.
I will let you know. I think we will handle the sales through the bsb website but I might do ad hoc sales in the mean time once we establish a price
I live in Kalamazoo and find Bell's overrated. If you come to Kzoo, don't skip Arcadia. Grand Rapids has a ton of good places but Founder's is the top of the heap

Wife and I made a trip to Munster (Three Floyds) and then continued up to Michigan City, IN last summer. Wanted to keep going but ran out of time. Will definitely check out Arcadia when we get back up that way. Good info. Thanx!
A fun thing to do in Michigan City is keep driving and don't stop until you get to Chicago
lol.
In Chicago, can confirm great breweries here.
No kidding? Are you from the area Jeremy? I live in central Illinois. We head up to Chicago about once a month... it's a 3 hour drive for us
Looking forward to Brew to Be Wild again at Lincoln Park Zoo in June. If you haven't gone, you gotta go. Monkeys and craft beer. Who knew they go well together.
Man, before I moved to the twin cities I was in Madison, Wi, a two hour drive to chicago
I like the local breweries we have in md
Heavy seas is one, dogfishhead though delaware
Key Brewing in Dundalk
Huge fan of Dogfish Head... 60 and 90 minute... 120 is a bit strong for me.
not gonna lie... I had to google where Dundalk was. :slightly_smiling_face:
Dogfish head was super great when I was in MD for work a few years ago
<@U3MRM1DDY> I was born and raised in Chicago
Was just by Madison on my way to GP Milwaukee couple months ago. Had to load up on Spotted Cow for a bunch of friend and family.
For my honeymoon my wife and I flew into Portland and just went up and down the coast going to different breweries like Lost Coast and Deschutes.
<@U3MRM1DDY> Spotted Cow is where it's at
I love 120 minute dogfishhead for the novelty. It gets me super wasted too
I have some Spotted Cow cans in my fridge. Go to New Glarus every few montgs
I love dogfishhead, only had the 120 once but it's crazy good
I have a bottle of 120 that I am aging
Deshutes is good stuff too.
One time i did a 60, 90, 120 in order. It was fun
Ha, did you start turning tricks in the parking lot after?
Because I would have been
I did it in the comfort of my own home
lol. that's one heck of a count up... it only takes one 120 to start making bad life decisions, lol.
I fought a school bus after I drank a 120
Haha
did you win?
Didnt know dogfishhead 120s had a following outside of my area to be honest
The only way to win is not to play
120 is world-renown by beer snobs
A lot of Dogfish Head is
There are a couple liquor stores in my area that carry it.

A bottle shop near me got 4 bottle and my friend and I got all of them

120s seem to go in and out of stock for long periods of time but i bought 12 of em the last time they had them in stock
<@U3NH6MY1X> Chicago is always good times. Be sure to check out the Lincoln Park Zoo, Brew to be Wild in June. I'll definitely be driving up for that.
I haven't been to Lincoln Park Zoo in years, I will have to do that
Yeah. They have over 40 micro breweries, food trucks and monkeys. June 17-18th, I believe.
Seems alright
THAT. is glorious. So many more options than we can get in Illinois
You can get all that in Chicago :)
Raison d'extra has a new label. Can't say I like it
I always fill up my fridge when I'm in Chicago... Here's what I picked up from my last trip to Binny's:
a lot of Three Floyd stuff from Munster, IN.... hard to find.
Rubaeus, eh? I think you would like Soft Parade
You ruin all of that by having Summer Shandy in there...
I noticed the Soft Parade in the pic you posted... Will probably give it a try.
Summer Shandy is a basic bitch beer but sometimes it is the only acceptable thing on tap
I love me some Leineys now and then, but it's hard to get behind fermented lemonade
Mix it with cherry wheat
lol. Top shelf is the stuff I give away. The rest is mine. :slightly_smiling_face:
That isn't how "top shelf" works at all
Lol
nope, but it's how my fridge works... :slightly_smiling_face:
There was a bar near where I used to work that had nothing good on tap so we mixed summer shandy and cherry wheat and it was drinkable. Good times
Last night I got soft parade mixed with Ciderboys. It tastes like fruit snacks
#softboys
lol. Mixing is good. I'll tip a little bit of Rubaeus  in a Chocolate porter from time to time...
Zombie dust is my favorite beer of all time. I remember having it at the brewpub before it had an official name
no kidding... ? Zombie Dust was what got me into craft beer. Can't get it in my area. Heck you can barely get it at the brewery.
all these talking reminds me of the worse beer I ever had, it was in montana, they were giving a free pint of it with every beer you ordered
it was awful

<@U3RJ9VDRT> was it PBR?
it was some local beer
like, I can drink PBR, I'm not happy about it, but I can drink it
I took one sip and I just stared at the glass
ha well put

"they had pounders for $1.50...and...well...I guess..."
